Site.Name: Urunga Lagoon 1
Name: Brendan Kelaher
Notes: This was carried out in eel grass (Zostera muelleri) directly adjacent to grey mangroves (Avicennia marina). The visibility was less than two metres. However, numerous silver biddys (Gerres subfasciatus) and yellow fin bream (Acanthopagrus australis) were observed biting the squid pops within minutes of deployment.
